    "caption": "Arctic armour in a ring of horns.",
    "shortDescription": "When wolves approach a musk ox herd, the adults don't run — they form a tight circle with calves in the centre, each adult facing outward with horns lowered, daring anything to try its luck. Their thick double-layered coats are so good at holding heat that the animals can stand perfectly still in blizzards. Fun fact: The soft undercoat of a musk ox, called qiviut, is one of the warmest natural fibres on Earth — warmer than sheep's wool by a factor of eight."
